 Responsible for management and execution of physical metallurgical coal &amp; coke market trades.
 Developing and maintaining a steady volume of monthly business, and has knowledge of risk management and full life-cycle trading principles
 Develop grow and maintain key customer relationships with Chinese steel mills, coke producers and any other prospective buyers.
 Assist in managing customer related settlement claims including, but not limited to; coal &amp; coke quality claims, settlements of vessel des/dem calculations, other operational matters etc.
 Develop a clear understanding of Chinese steel customer뭩 demand requirements and coking coal blends and position CITIC to develop sustainable business with target customers.
 Develop an in-depth understanding of imported seaborne coking coal market dynamics including; coal specifications, competitor analysis, tracking of total volumes being imported and end user sales, tracking of types of coals being imported, tracking of prices of both domestic Chinese and international prices
 Keep track of market movements and information as well as pricing curves and analysis to ensure profitable trading portfolio in order to capitalise on any opportunity
 Negotiate and finalise contracts and supply agreements with customers, whilst working closely with the operational and logistics team to ensure timely and smooth trades
 Develop strategies to limit/manage pricing exposure risks
 Evaluate and manage supply chain opportunities (logistics service offerings for select customers, stock and sell opportunities etc).
 Other duties as required